sec.p:
In development of a FFS assessment further work will be required, which includes:


revised test rig where the corrosion is actually simulated;

more practical testing of a many sizes and materials of nuts to find any possible correlations between allowable corrosion levels and geometry or material;

more in depth FEA analysis of the flange system, which can model the process of corrosion so the relaxation can be accurately measured.
This report covers ground work required to understand the mechanical limitations of the system and can be used as a foundation for further work to develop a full Fitness-For-Service assessment. Methods of measuring the corrosion are available, as are methods of corrosion prediction so there needs to be more work done to understand the mechanical limitations of all nut sizes when corroded. The results from this work may seem predictable to a point; however, what came from this work was a clear understanding of the damage mechanism as a function of material loss. The study managed to identify when the assembly failed and the manner of the failure, information not previously known.
